attributes.description: Agentcore runtime details dashboard showcasing runtime performance and operational health.

params.markdown:
# Agentcore runtime

This dashboard provides insights into the following:
- Agent runtime invocations and session metrics across endpoints
- Error monitoring, including system errors, user errors, and overall error trends
- Performance analysis with latency, duration, and throttling metrics
- Endpoint-specific analytics showing top performers by invocation and session counts

embeddableConfig.title: Invocations
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the trend of invocations across all resources

embeddableConfig.title: Sessions
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the trend of agent sessions initiated.

embeddableConfig.title: Top invocation and error summary - by endpoint
embeddableConfig.description: Displays the top 10 invocations, sessions, user errors, system errors, and average latency - by endpoint

embeddableConfig.title: Top 10 endpoints - by invocation count
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the end points with most invocations in the selected time range

embeddableConfig.title: Invocations
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the trend of the total number of invocations grouped by endpoint

embeddableConfig.title: Sessions
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the trend of agent sessions initiated grouped by endpoint.

embeddableConfig.title: System errors
embeddableConfig.description: Server-side errors indicating infrastructure or service issues

embeddableConfig.title: User errors
embeddableConfig.description: Client-side errors resulting from invalid requests.

embeddableConfig.title: Top 10 endpoints by errors
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the top 10 endpoints by the number of invocation errors.

embeddableConfig.title: Error breakdown: Total vs System vs User
embeddableConfig.description: Trend of overall errors compared to user and system errors during agent execution

embeddableConfig.title: Throttles
embeddableConfig.description: Requests throttled due to exceeding allowed TPS or quota limits

embeddableConfig.title: Latency
embeddableConfig.description: The total time elapsed between receiving the request and sending the final response token. Represents complete end-to-end processing time of the request.

embeddableConfig.title: Duration
embeddableConfig.description: Average duration of agent execution for each request.

embeddableConfig.title: Top 10 endpoints by latency
embeddableConfig.description: Shows the top 10 endpoints by invocation latency

embeddableConfig.title: Latency vs Duration
embeddableConfig.description: Duration is the average duration of agent execution for each request. Latency is the average time elapsed between receiving the request and sending the final response token.

query.esql:
FROM logs-aws_bedrock_agentcore.runtime_application_logs-default
| KEEP @timestamp, aws.bedrock_agentcore.request_id, aws.bedrock_agentcore.endpoint_name, aws.bedrock_agentcore.agent_name, aws.bedrock_agentcore.request_payload.prompt, aws.bedrock_agentcore.resource_arn, trace.id, aws.bedrock_agentcore.session_id
| SORT @timestamp ASC
| RENAME aws.bedrock_agentcore.request_id as `Request ID`, aws.bedrock_agentcore.endpoint_name AS `Endpoint Name`, aws.bedrock_agentcore.agent_name AS `Agent Name`, aws.bedrock_agentcore.request_payload.prompt AS `Prompt`, aws.bedrock_agentcore.resource_arn AS `Resource ARN`, trace.id AS `Trace ID`, aws.bedrock_agentcore.session_id AS `Session ID`
